# Clusters — all-purpose vs. job

A **cluster** is cloud VMs running Spark together: one **driver** that coordinates and one or more **workers** that do the parallel work.

## All-purpose — interactive

Created by hand, notebooks attached, stays up while you explore; multiple users share it. For **dev, ad-hoc analysis, and debugging** — bills at a **higher DBU rate**.

## Job — ephemeral

A Lakeflow Job creates one per run and tears it down when the run finishes. Each run is **isolated**, at a **lower DBU rate**. For **scheduled production ETL**.

**Rule of thumb:** dev and exploration → all-purpose; scheduled production → job. Running production on an all-purpose cluster costs more and loses per-run isolation.
